The paper deals with the problem of hand segmentation in mixed reality, which is a computer vision task and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also applies the proposed architecture to road segmentation, which is a robotics task and falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed architecture is a deep learning model, and hence, it could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with image and video processing, which could also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
